Job Description:
Business Analyst - INF003030

Employment Type: Permanent Full-time
Location(s): SK-Rgna-Regina
Ministry: 027 Parks Culture and Sport
Salary Range: $34.028 -$42.641 Hourly
Grade: SGEU.10.
About Us
The Ministry of Parks, Culture & Sport's mission is to contribute to Saskatchewan’s high quality of life, instill pride and enhance the province’s cultural, artistic, recreational and social life through management of the Saskatchewan provincial parks system, the provision of arts, culture, recreation, sport and tourism opportunities, access to French language services through stewardship of provincial heritage resources. The Ministry also manages and enhances Saskatchewan’s provincial parks system and the Royal Saskatchewan Museum, conserving ecosystems and cultural resources and providing recreational and interpretive opportunities for visitors.
The Opportunity
The Strategic and Corporate Services Branch is seeking a highly motivated, results-oriented individual to fill a key position as a Business Analyst. In this diverse role, you will lead the Ministry’s IT strategic planning, and provide strategic advice on a variety of technology-related projects and initiativese. This ranges from iniating Service Level Requests, to project requirements gathering, to project mangement. You will also be the primary contact for the ministry’s use of SharePoint providing on-going support, oversight, governance and functionality enhancements for existing and new sites. This is a diverse role that will require frequent consultations and with a variety of stakeholders, as well as undertaking research and business needs analysis to find solutions to problems encountered by clients.
 Reporting to the Director, Financial Services, the successful candidate will:
Engage with ministry staff and stakeholders to analyze current and future business needs and requirements;
Develop comprehensive business requirements and recommendations to meet the needs of business clients;
Research and analyze the "best fit for future" business solution concepts and designs;
Facilitate the implementation of business improvement and IT projects to improve functionality of ministry programs and processes including processing service level requests;
Act as Ministry liaison between Ministry and ITD, as well as between Corporate Services and Ministry Branches for IT related issues. This includes responding to requests for input, reporting on new IT initiatives, and overseeing participation in pilot applications;
Lead the Ministry’s Information Technology Operating Committee (ITOC) and SharePoint Governance Committee (SGC); and
Establish quality standards to ensure consistency and make recommendations for changes and improvements.

Ideal Candidate
In order to be successful in the role, the ideal candidate will have:
A comprehensive understanding of project management, change management and continuous improvement principles;
A comprehensive knowledge of business needs analysis/business process improvement methodologies, tools and processes;
The ability to identify, clarify and analyze issues, concerns or problems in order to provide options and recommendations and/or implement solutions;
The ability to consult and communicate effectively with a variety of technical colleagues and non-technical clients to understand their business line;
The ability to build and maintain co-operative and collaborative relationships with colleagues, team members, business clients, external stakeholders and service providers; and
An understanding of the ministry’s programs, services and associated legislation.

Typically, the knowledge and competencies for this position would be acquired through the completion of a university degree in Business Administration, business analysis certification, or an equivalent combination of education and experience.
The ministry sees importinace in the core values of: respect and integrity; serving citizens, practicing excellence and innovation; and acting as One Team, including participating in and contributing to an inclusive workplace culture.
What We Offer:
Dynamic, challenging work for talented individuals;
A competitive salary;
Comprehensive benefits package including pension;
Paid vacation, earned days off (EDO) and other types of leave (maternity/paternity/adoption, family/personal leave, sick leave);
Inclusive work environments;
Advancement opportunities; and,
Flexible work arrangements.

We are committed to workplace diversity.
