Responsibilities
The successful candidate will be accountable to the Manager, Financial Reporting and working with management of specific areas the key responsibilities include:


Assisting with the budgeting, forecasting and monitoring systems and processes in support of decision-making, and develop strategic opportunities for business improvements;
Recommend and implement change, identify training requirements, develop business process improvement, carryout business case analysis, identify potential risks, assist in the development of business plans;
Assisting with strategic financial analysis as required to drive improved decision making;
Preparation, analysis, and presentation of monthly, quarterly, and annual operating results to Deans, Budget officers and Director, Financial Services;
Developing and maintaining an effective working relationship with internal and external stakeholders;
Providing sound advice and guidance to areas you support on all account matters including financial systems, record keeping, analysis and reporting;
Under the direction of the Director, Financial Services and working with the Finance team assist in the formulation of system-wide accounting policies, procedures and controls;

